Base layer styles (`@layer base`, `tw-animate-css` import) were previously hardcoded in `updateBaseLayerPlugin`, a PostCSS plugin that ran on every shadcn add command. This moves them to the `registry:style` item's css field, for instance `new-york`, making them registry-driven and decoupled from the CLI.

The CLI no longer injects the following base layer styles:

```css
@layer base {
  * {
    @apply border-border outline-ring/50;
  }
  body {
    @apply bg-background text-foreground;
  }
}
```

## Test

Use the following command to test:

```bash
npx shadcn@3.8.5-beta.0 init
```

We have added our two custom registry in your directory.json

@shadcn-space
@sahdcn-dashboard

Thanks for your review.

## Magic UI Pro Registry

This PR adds Magic UI Pro as a trusted registry.

The entire registry is available to view at https://pro.magicui.design/registry.json

The individual components are only available using the bearer token authentication scheme by sending token to the `https://pro.magicui.design/registry/{name}` API route. More details [here](https://pro.magicui.design/docs/installation) 

## Manual Installation

Add the following to your `components.json`
```
{
  "registries": {
    "@magicui-pro": {
      "url": "https://pro.magicui.design/registry/{name}",
      "headers": {
        "Authorization": "Bearer ${MAGICUI_PRO_REGISTRY_TOKEN}"
      }
    }
  }
}

This is a simple refactor to the form component which gets rid of the type assertion of initial values of the form contexts.  In this PR we initialize `FormFieldContext` and `FormItemContext` with `null` values rather than empty object with type assertion.

**Additional info**
Because of the type assertion I was getting lint error on the following line for [@typescript-eslint/no-unnecessary-condition](https://typescript-eslint.io/rules/no-unnecessary-condition) rule, which logically should not happen.

```
  if (!fieldContext) {
    throw new Error('useFormField should be used within <FormField>');
  }
```

